Update. 02/22/18 This site is totally overgrown, and is no longer because the navy has closed it down.

&nbsp;

Portage Beach is a quiet, protected campsite nestled among nootka rose and hawthorne trees. Watch the current change in Portage Canal or walk the hiking trails along the shore. A good alternative to Kinney Point or Oak Bay when the winds are blowing from the southeast.

On summer days, visitors to Shaw County Park may find pleasurable swimming at Indian Cove. Warmer water temperatures are created by exposure to long hours of sunlight and the cove's shallow depths. The scene is completed by the beautiful sandy beach. Once a military reservation, the 60-acre property is now preserved by San Juan County Parks. The park has 3,249 feet of shoreline.

[ngg src="galleries" ids="2" display="basic_thumbnail"]&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

A pleasant glide on a flood tide takes you in the long throat of Stuart Island to the western most campground on the Cascadia Marine Trail. Time your arrival and departure to the tides to avoid a long haul to the campsite.

&nbsp;

Allow time for game spotting as you pass Spieden Island, once an African game farm. Landing on Spieden is prohibited. The currents can be rapid along the island, and rough at the northeastern tip.

&nbsp;

Roche Harbor has let us put a launch-and-land site from the south side of the resort. Overnight parking fees apply.

&nbsp;

Hike up the stairs from the campsite for a nice view of the harbor or head out to the lighthouse.

